# Location design (LOCKED)

Read `LOCATION_DESIGN.md` before adding or changing any location.

- One illustrated screen = one visitable scene. No scrolling maps, procedural cities, or open-world systems.
- Every new location requires: **visual anchor**, **pseudo-animation** (overlay), **interaction** (hotspot), **observation** (short fragment in copy).
- Add locations one at a time via `data/screens.json` + background art. Update `DOOM_DANCE.md`.
- Atmosphere over mechanics. Places should feel like they existed before the player and will after they leave.
